  <note line="3" original="āpattidiṭṭhī (sī.)" reference-line="3" id="0">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">āpattidiṭṭhi</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="sī." source="sri lanka">āpattidiṭṭhī</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous> samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme. Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpanno hoti. So tassā āpattiyā āpattidiṭṭhi </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="11" original="āyasmantā (ka.)" reference-line="9" id="1">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">āyasmanto</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">āyasmantā</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous>Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpanno hoti. So tassā āpattiyā anāpattidiṭṭhi hoti, aññe bhikkhū tassā āpattiyā āpattidiṭṭhino honti. So ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu te bhikkhū evaṃ jānāti – ‘ime kho āyasmanto </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="19" original="te (syā.)" reference-line="11" id="2">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">ete</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">te</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous> so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca – te, bhante, ukkhittānuvattakā bhikkhū tattheva antosīmāya uposathaṃ karonti, saṅghakammaṃ karonti. Mayaṃ pana ukkhepakā bhikkhū nissīmaṃ gantvā uposathaṃ karoma, saṅghakammaṃ karomā’’ti. Te ce, bhikkhu, ukkhittānuvattakā bhikkhū tattheva antosīmāya uposathaṃ karissanti, saṅghakammaṃ karissanti, yathā mayā ñatti ca anussāvanā ca paññattā, tesaṃ tāni kammāni dhammikāni kammāni bhavissa’’nti akuppāni ṭhānārahāni. Tumhe ce, bhikkhu, ukkhepakā bhikkhū tattheva antosīmāya uposathaṃ karissatha, saṅghakammaṃ karissatha, yathā mayā ñatti ca anussāvanā ca paññattā, tumhākampi tāni kammāni dhammikāni kammāni bhavissanti akuppāni ṭhānārahāni. Taṃ kissa hetu? Nānāsaṃvāsakā ete </previous>
  </note>
